\nBackend Setup\n- Install and configure stripe Node SDK\n- Store STRIPE_SECRET_KEY, STRIPE_WEBHOOK_SECRET, and public NEXT_PUBLIC_STRIPE_PUBLISHABLE_KEY in environment variables\n- Create or sync Stripe Products and Prices for all three tiers (idempotent seed script)\n- Create a Stripe Customer on user registration or first subscription action, persist stripeCustomerId in the subscriptions table\n\nAPI Routes (Next.js Route Handlers under /api/billing/)\n- POST /api/billing/checkout — create a Stripe Checkout Session for new subscriptions; redirect to Stripe-hosted page\n- POST /api/billing/portal — create a Stripe Customer Portal session for self-service management; redirect to Stripe-hosted portal\n- POST /api/billing/webhook — receive and verify Stripe webhook events (use raw body + HMAC signature validation consistent with existing HMAC signing pattern)\n- GET /api/billing/subscription — return current user's subscription status, plan, and period details\n- GET /api/billing/invoices — return paginated list of past invoices for the authenticated user\n\nWebhook Events to Handle\n- checkout.session.completed — provision subscription, update DB\n- customer.subscription.updated — sync plan changes, status, and billing cycle\n- customer.subscription.deleted — downgrade to free, mark canceled\n- invoice.payment_succeeded — record invoice, update period dates\n- invoice.payment_failed — mark subscription as past_due, trigger notification\n- customer.subscription.trial_ending_soon — send reminder email via Resend\n\n---\n\nUSER-FACING SUBSCRIPTION MANAGEMENT\n\nSettings Page — Billing & Subscription (/settings/billing)\n- Current plan summary card: plan name, billing cycle, renewal date, status badge (active / past_due / canceled)\n- Upgrade / Downgrade CTA: opens Stripe Customer Portal or Checkout Session depending on current state\n- Cancel subscription option with confirmation modal: show what access will be lost, confirm cancel-at-period-end behavior (no immediate cutoff)\n- Reactivation prompt if subscription is canceled but within grace period\n- Annual vs. monthly billing toggle with savings callout (e.g., \"Save 30% annually\")\n\nBilling History Section\n- Paginated table of past invoices: date, amount, status (paid / open / void), billing period\n- Download PDF link per invoice (Stripe-hosted PDF URL)\n- View hosted invoice link (Stripe-hosted invoice page)\n- Empty state for Free tier users with no billing history\n\nPlan Comparison Modal\n- Side-by-side feature matrix for Free / Standard / Pro\n- Highlight current plan\n- CTA per tier (current plan indicator, upgrade button, or contact sales if applicable)\n\n---\n\nFEATURE GATING\n\n- Create a server-side utility (e.g., lib/subscription.ts) that resolves the current user's plan from the DB (not Stripe live API, to avoid latency)\n- Expose a useSubscription() React hook (via TanStack React Query) for client-side gating\n- Apply gates at both API route level (return 403 with plan upgrade prompt) and UI level (lock icons, upgrade prompts on restricted features)\n- Free tier restrictions enforced: board/card count limits, capture limits, MCP access, AI features\n- Degraded-but-not-broken UX on downgrade: existing data remains visible in read-only state where limits are exceeded; no silent data deletion\n\n---\n\nADMIN CONSOLE\n\nAdmin Route: /admin/subscriptions (protect with role-based middleware; admin role stored on user record)\n\nSubscription Overview Dashboard\n- Summary metrics cards: total active subscriptions, MRR (calculated from active subscription prices), breakdown by plan (Free / Standard / Pro counts), churn count (canceled last 30 days)\n- Full subscriptions table with columns: user email, plan, billing cycle, status, current period end, Stripe customer ID (linked to Stripe dashboard), joined date\n- Filter by plan, status, and date range\n- Search by email or Stripe customer ID\n- Paginated with configurable page size\n\nAdmin Actions (per subscription row)\n- View full subscription detail modal: all DB fields + link to Stripe customer dashboard\n- Manually override plan (e.g., grant Pro access for a support case) with reason field stored in audit trail\n- Cancel subscription immediately or at period end\n- Trigger refund (calls Stripe Refunds API) for most recent invoice with confirmation modal\n- Send reactivation email manually via Resend\n\nAudit Trail Integration\n- All admin-initiated subscription changes must write to the existing immutable audit trail (consistent with the Immutable Audit Trail for Sensitive Operations feature already in scope)\n- Log: adminUserId, targetUserId, action, previousValue, newValue, reason, timestamp\n\n---\n\nTRANSACTIONAL EMAILS (via Resend)\n\n- Subscription confirmed (new signup or upgrade): plan name, features unlocked, next billing date\n- Plan downgraded: what was lost, what remains, link to reactivate\n- Payment failed: amount due, retry date, link to update payment method in Customer Portal\n- Subscription canceled: effective date, data retention policy, reactivation CTA\n- Trial ending soon (if trials are offered): days remaining, upgrade CTA\n- Invoice paid receipt: amount, billing period, PDF download link\n\n---\n\nEDGE CASES & CONSIDERATIONS\n\n- Webhook idempotency: check stripeInvoiceId / stripeSubscriptionId before inserting to prevent duplicate processing on Stripe retry\n- Clock skew: use Stripe event timestamps as source of truth, not server time\n- Proration: Stripe handles proration automatically on mid-cycle upgrades/downgrades; surface prorated amount in confirmation UI before user confirms plan change\n- Failed payment recovery: expose \"Update Payment Method\" deep link into Customer Portal; surface past_due banner in app header\n- Concurrent webhook events: use DB-level upsert (ON CONFLICT) for subscription sync to avoid race conditions\n- Free tier users: always have a subscriptions row with plan = free and no Stripe IDs; do not attempt Stripe API calls for these users\n- User deletion: extend existing Account Deletion with Cascading Data Removal to cancel active Stripe subscription and delete Stripe Customer before removing DB records\n- Test mode: all Stripe keys and webhook endpoints must support a STRIPE_TEST_MODE environment flag with test clock support for QA\n- GDPR / export: include subscription history and invoices in the existing Full Data Export feature\n\n---\n\nACCEPTANCE CRITERIA\n\n- A new user lands on Free tier automatically upon registration with no Stripe interaction required\n- A Free user can upgrade to Standard or Pro via Checkout and land back in the app with the correct plan reflected within 5 seconds of webhook processing\n- A Pro user can downgrade to Standard via Customer Portal; access is adjusted at period end, not immediately\n- A user can view at least 12 months of invoice history with working PDF download links\n- Cancellation sets cancelAtPeriodEnd = true; user retains access until period end; banner warns of upcoming loss of access\n- All webhook events are processed idempotently with no duplicate invoice records under load\n- Admin can view all subscriptions, filter/search, manually override a plan, and trigger a refund — all actions logged to audit trail\n- Feature gates return 403 from API routes with a structured error payload including requiredPlan field\n- All transactional emails render correctly in dark and light mode (consistent with Dark Mode Polish feature)\n- Full test coverage of webhook handler using Stripe CLI event fixtures",
