  "summary": "## Summary: Stripe Subscription Management System\n\n### Changes Implemented\n\n**Plan Configuration (Free/Standard/Pro tiers):**\n- Rewrote `lib/stripe-plans.ts` with three tiers: Free ($0), Standard ($12/mo or $99/yr), Pro ($29/mo or $249/yr)\n- Added `PlanKey` type, `PLAN_ORDER`, `resolvePlanKey()`, `getFeaturesForPlan()`, `getRequiredPlanForFeature()` utilities\n- Each plan includes `featureMatrix` (for UI comparison tables) and `limits` (board/card/capture counts, MCP access level, AI features flag)\n\n**Subscription Access & Feature Gating:**\n- Updated `lib/access.ts` with `getUserPlanInfo()` that resolves the user's effective plan from DB, `UserPlanInfo` interface\n- Free-tier features are always accessible even without a subscription record\n- Created `lib/subscription-gate.ts` with `requireFeature()` and `requirePlan()` — API route middleware that returns 403 with structured error payload including `requiredPlan`, `requiredPlanName`, `currentPlan`, `currentPlanName`\n\n**Client-Side Hook:**\n- Created `lib/hooks/useSubscription.ts` — `useSubscription()` React hook that fetches plan info from `/api/billing/subscription`, exposes `planKey`, `planName`, `hasFeature()`, `loading`, `refetch()`\n- Duplicated feature lists client-side to avoid importing server-only code\n\n**Webhook Handler Enhancements:**\n- Updated `app/api/webhooks/stripe/route.ts` to handle `customer.subscription.trial_will_end` event\n- Added transactional email sends on: checkout completed (confirmation), invoice paid (receipt), payment failed (action required), subscription deleted (cancellation notice), trial ending soon\n- Added `getUserEmailBySubscriptionId()` helper for email lookups\n\n**Transactional Emails:**\n- Created `lib/billing-emails.ts` with 6 email templates via Resend: subscription confirmed, plan downgraded, payment failed, subscription canceled, trial ending soon, invoice paid receipt\n- Graceful no-op when `RESEND_API_KEY` is not configured\n\n**Billing API:**\n- Updated `app/api/billing/subscription/route.ts` to return `planKey` in response using `resolvePlanKey()`\n\n**Pricing Page:**\n- Updated `app/(marketing)/pricing/PricingClient.tsx` to show Free/Standard/Pro tiers with correct pricing ($0/$12/$29)\n- Free tier shows \"Current default\" button (disabled), save badge shows \"Save 30%\" for annual\n\n**Billing Settings Page:**\n- Enhanced `app/(app)/billing/BillingClient.tsx` with:\n  - Past-due payment banner with update payment CTA\n  - Plan comparison modal with side-by-side feature matrix across all 3 tiers\n  - Current plan indicator in comparison table\n  - Improved cancel confirmation showing what features will be lost\n  - Empty state messaging for Free tier users\n\n**Admin Subscriptions Console:**\n- Enhanced `app/(app)/admin/subscriptions/SubscriptionsClient.tsx` with:\n  - Action buttons per row: View, Cancel, Refund\n  - Detail modal showing all subscription fields + links\n  - Cancel modal with immediate/period-end toggle and reason field\n  - Change plan modal with price ID selector\n  - Refund confirmation modal\n  - Feedback toast notifications\n  - Search by Stripe subscription ID in addition to name/email\n\n**Types:**\n- Added `PlanKey` type to `types/index.ts`\n\n### Files Modified\n- `lib/stripe-plans.ts` — Rewritten with Free/Standard/Pro tiers, limits, feature matrix\n- `lib/access.ts` — Added `getUserPlanInfo()`, updated `hasAccess()` for free-tier fallback\n- `lib/hooks/useSubscription.ts` — New file: client-side subscription hook\n- `lib/subscription-gate.ts` — New file: API route feature/plan gating middleware\n- `lib/billing-emails.ts` — New file: transactional email templates via Resend\n- `app/api/webhooks/stripe/route.ts` — Added trial_will_end handler, email sends\n- `app/api/billing/subscription/route.ts` — Added planKey to response\n- `app/(marketing)/pricing/PricingClient.tsx` — Updated to Free/Standard/Pro tiers\n- `app/(app)/billing/BillingClient.tsx` — Added plan comparison modal, past-due banner\n- `app/(app)/admin/subscriptions/SubscriptionsClient.tsx` — Added action modals (view, cancel, change plan, refund)\n- `types/index.ts` — Added PlanKey type\n\n### Notes for Developer\n- **Environment variables needed**: `STRIPE_PRICE_STANDARD_MONTHLY`, `STRIPE_PRICE_STANDARD_ANNUAL`, `STRIPE_PRICE_PRO_MONTHLY`, `STRIPE_PRICE_PRO_ANNUAL` (and corresponding `NEXT_PUBLIC_` variants for client components)\n- The old env vars `STRIPE_PRICE_STARTER_*` and `STRIPE_PRICE_ENT_*` are no longer referenced\n- Database schema was NOT changed — the existing `subscriptions`, `stripeWebhookEvents`, and `adminActionLogs` tables are sufficient. No migration needed.\n- Free tier users have no subscription row in the DB (handled gracefully by `getUserPlanInfo()` returning `planKey: \"free\"`)\n- The `requireFeature()` / `requirePlan()` middleware can be added to any API route: `const gate = await requireFeature(\"brain_chat\"); if (gate) return gate;`\n- `Infinity` values in plan limits are only used server-side for comparisons, never serialized to JSON\n- Stripe webhook secret should be set via `STRIPE_WEBHOOK_SECRET` env var\n- Resend emails gracefully skip when `RESEND_API_KEY` is not configured"
}